itemListElement.name: Pacific Science Center General Exhibit Admission

name: Pacific Science Center General Exhibit Admission
description: Pacific Science Center near the Space Needle in Seattle Center is Washington’s leading attraction for fun and engaging experiences for families and guests of all ages. Explore hundreds of interactive exhibits, wander among fluttering tropical butterflies, tinker with reusable products, touch live marine animals, come face-to-face with prehistoric dinosaurs, travel to outer space in the planetarium, rock out to a dazzling daytime laser show, and so much more. For an additional fee, guests can experience Pacific Science Center’s two IMAX® Theaters.

review.name: Old /Not well maintained
review.reviewBody:
If you have visited nice museums, this is
Not for you . If your child has not been to a museum before, I guess will be fine. My 4yr was exited about dinosaurs, you are going to be disappointed.

Be aware:
-parking structure, pricey and tight 
-gas station around the corner with weird people. You know what I meant regarding safety/drugs
-Museum hasn’t been remodeled, most exhibitions are off or broken. No staff around
-looks old , needs to be remodeled 
-expensive for what you are going to see! In 1 hr you already see everything . Spaces are big but exhibitions are small . Lack of inside light, not clean
-tide pool have water wash no soap
-outside water exhibitions looks like they are stock in early 2000s , rusty, paint less, broken
-Butterflies is one of the areas where staff is and extreme clean
-3D printing area, have staff around but other than that is like you see everything old

Good luck. I don’t recommend this museum. Everyone has own personal perspective. For us, 2 small kids/2 adults around $110, 1hr to complete the visit and we learned more at home than with this visit.

review.name: Better for younger kids
review.reviewBody: We have visited a lot of science centers, and I hate giving lower reviews to a place of learning, but my 12yo son and I were a little disappointed. The general admission ticket only really gets you in to permanent exhibits and a lot of them we've seen in other science centers around the country. We didn't find much to be unique and we didn't find much for teens. We were there maybe 1.5hrs. Geared towards younger kids for sure.

review.name: Not good for a solo adult
review.reviewBody: Very bad for adults. Quite bad planetarium, the exhibits are really basic (more like toddler/young elementary focused) and the laser show really hurt my eyes. I am an adult solo traveler who loves like amusement parks, aquariums, etc. and this was not good for an adult!! Save your money and go elsewhere if you don't have kids.

review.name: BRAINS, BRAINS, BRAINS!
review.reviewBody: Zombies would have been right at home! We visited Brain Fest to geek out on brains and we weren't disappointed! First, there were multiple stations with brain related activities and sometimes, real brains! We saw a real brain dissection where we learned why the term grey matter exists (tho its sort of pinky brown) AND we held a T-rex 3D printed brain-turns out that their small brain packed a powerful ability to smell. Kids loved having printed guides to all of the stations so they could collect stamps along the way and not miss a cool experience. PacSci has a new exhibit, Brainy Bodies, with some very interactive experiences that worked really well with this event. I struggled with one brain interactive until a child about 4 years old showed me the way. I plan to go back and tackle that one when fewer people are watching me...Shout out to PacSci, Allen Institute and University of Washington folks for making Brain Fest 2025 happen. Truly memorable! And folks, you only get one brain so wear those helmets!

review.name: Great place for kids
review.reviewBody: This place is great! This is a must stop place for our daughter! She is 4 this year and she had a blast here at the science center! There’s plenty to do in there and she loves the toddler section! This place is great for all ages and depends on the age of the child, there’s plenty to explore for all ages! We haven’t tried the movies but will definitely love to try them when my daughter is a little bigger!

review.name: Science museum
review.reviewBody:
Very nice experience.  Better with younger children but good for all ages
Butterflies exhibit, Planetarium and Laser show too.

review.name: Always something to learn
review.reviewBody: PacSci ignites curiosity in every child and adult, fueling a passion for discovery, experimentation, and critical thinking in all of us.

review.name: Great For All Ages
review.reviewBody: Lots of fun for all ages.  Butterfly House has species from all over the world.  There is a dinosaur section for the young ones

review.name: A day well spent
review.reviewBody: This was a day well spent. Based on all there was to do, I knew it was going to be an all day visit, which it was. It is a museum for children (I wasn't sure if it was also going to be an adult museum, but it was really for kids). My 7 year old loved it. I thought that the actual museum was just ok -- it wasn't super large. But all the add ons made it super special (the planetarium, the laser show, and the IMAX, all of which we did). While the planetarium and laser show are included with the tickets, you have to reserve them when you get your tickets. So it's important to either buy your tickets in advance (I think the planetarium can't be reserved in advance before the day of but I'm not sure, we bought our tickets in person the morning of) or arrive early day of. Sure enough, some of the things were full by noon and I was glad we started early. It's a full day to get in an IMAX show (extra cost), the planetarium, and the laser show, which are all timed tickets. The butterfly area is super cool. They had a show of illusions which was super fun. There's a room of hands on physics things that are super fun for kids. We stayed until they closed and we started shortly after they opened. It's a little intense with kids running around, but it's manageable. They do not have a place to eat, so be sure to pack lunches. We didn't have time to leave and get food, so we wound up just eating the snacks I brought. My daughter also caught a cold after being there, which makes sense with all the kids and their germs, so be prepared for some exposures, and perhaps plan the timing in your trip accordingly.

review.name: Don't bother
review.reviewBody: complete and total trash. discriminatory and run by overly sensitive liberal who want to get rid of any who is different

description:
Discover the natural beauty of the Pacific Northwest with our Seattle Audio Tour Bundle: Mount Rainier, Olympic National Park and North Cascades National Park! Explore the majestic peaks, lush forests, and stunning landscapes of these iconic parks at your own pace. With our easy-to-use audio guides, you'll learn fascinating facts, hear engaging stories, and uncover hidden gems along the way.

Marvel at Mount Rainier's towering glaciers, alpine meadows, and diverse wildlife. Experience the tranquil beauty of Olympic National Park's rainforests, rugged coastline, and serene lakes. Our tours provide insider tips and historical insights, making your adventure both educational and enjoyable.

Perfect for families, nature lovers, and outdoor enthusiasts, our audio tours offer the flexibility to explore these breathtaking parks whenever you choose. 

*Download the Shaka Guide app to access the purchased tours

review.name: Excellent audio tour!
review.reviewBody: We had an excellent time. The audio tour was extremely helpful in deciding what to do next. The information was helpful, educational, and very fun for adults and children!

name: Seattle Summer Views Cruise
description: Experience our newest voyage this summer, our Summer Views Cruise! This 1.5-hour cruise is the perfect place to bask in golden hour as the sun begins to set. Head up to the top deck to take in that summer breeze and enjoy locally sourced beverages and bites while the captain takes you on a surprise route around Puget Sound and shares their favorite landmarks. This cruise is unique in that narration will be minimal so that you can socialize and take in the sights — like breathtaking views of the Seattle skyline and the Olympic Mountains.

name: Hoppin' Seattle Guided Brew Tour
description:
Sip your way through Seattle! Our Seattle Brewery Tour is a unique experience that offers our guests an opportunity to visit and learn about various breweries and their beer-making processes. This brew tour provides a chance to learn about the history of Seattle and insight into various local ingredients and beer styles. 

Our brew tour combines education, variety, atmosphere, interaction, socialization and local flavors. Whether you're a beer enthusiast or just looking for a fun and engaging activity, our brew tour is sure to leave you with lasting memories and a newfound appreciation for the art of brewing.

itemListElement.name: Roasted in Seattle: Bean to Cup Coffee Tour

name: Roasted in Seattle: Bean to Cup Coffee Tour
description:
Delve deep into the heart of Seattle's renowned coffee culture on this bean-to-cup coffee tour, crafted especially for aficionados of the rich aromas and flavors of the coffee world, which is alive and thriving on the bustling streets of Seattle. Let your senses be tantalized by the roasting beans, aromatic brews, and picturesque landscapes that define this vibrant city's coffee scene.

This 2-hour walking tour will take you to a number of iconic roasteries and favorite coffee shops around downtown. You'll begin at Anchorhead Coffee, and from there will sip your way through the best coffee in Seattle. You'll even get to visit the very first Starbucks, where it all began! Whether you're a coffee afficionado or just a social sipper, this immersive and unique adventure through Seattle will leave your taste buds tingling!

review.name: Coffee fun and history!
review.reviewBody: Zach did an outstanding job providing a thorough knowledge of coffee and the roasting and brewing process. The tour combines the history of coffee with unique tastings mixed in. The cinnamon roll tasting at Storyville was phenomenal! You will also get some history and a walk-thru of Pike Place Market on your coffee journey. Thank you Zach!

review.name: Great experience for locals and travelers!
review.reviewBody: What a great experience! Our guide Zach was friendly, organized, and knowledgeable. He took us to 8 different locations around Pike Place Market, with 4 coffee tastings at 4 different local coffee shops. We also had a pastry tasting at a 5th café. I don't even drink coffee, but made an exception and enjoyed the buzz : ) Totally recommend it!

review.name: Great Coffee Experience
review.reviewBody: Great Tour.  Great coffee.  Zach was very knowledgeable and a great tour guide.  We learned about different kinds of beans, the different styles of coffee, their origins, and a whole lot more that we didn’t know about Coffee while having fun and experiencing coffee at different shops with a very nice group of people.

review.name: Family lives for coffee
review.reviewBody: Our guide was amazing. Educational and enjoyable!! Even the tea drinkers enjoyed the time. Going through Pike market was a highlight

review.name: Wonderful Tour
review.reviewBody: Great tour guide and history of coffee plus wonderful tastings at each place.  Found some new coffee places to visit on our next trip to Seattle.

itemListElement.name: z OLD & INACTIVE VERSION ... on Seattle’s Majestic Puget Sound

name: z OLD & INACTIVE VERSION ... on Seattle’s Majestic Puget Sound
description:
INACTIVE VERSION - of being carried by the wind, just as Peter Puget was when he mapped these waters back in 1792. From Seattle’s Shilshole Bay Marina we sail west across Puget Sound toward the magnificent Olympic Mountains. Along the way we will watch for orcas, schools of our local porpoises, sea lions, harbor seals, bald eagles, great blue herons, and other wildlife. On the Sunset Cruise, we’ll enjoy the light show as the sun drops behind the well-named Mount Olympus and other peaks in the Olympic Range and illuminates feathery horizon clouds into glorious colors.

Captain Grant, who holds a 100-ton Master of Inland Waters License from the U.S. Coast Guard, is dedicated to sharing the joy of being on the water with others. A former reporter for the Seattle Times, former Science and Medical writer for the Associated Press, and author of four books (one of which was named one of the year’s 10 Best nonfiction books by the American Library Association) Grant is a natural story teller.

itemListElement.name: Explore Snoqualmie, Waterfalls and an Ancient Forest

name: Explore Snoqualmie, Waterfalls and an Ancient Forest
description:
This excursion is meticulously designed to foster a profound connection with nature, facilitating tranquility and serenity through the forest's inherent calmness. Tailored to accommodate varying ages and fitness levels, this bespoke experience promises inclusivity.

Commencing in the morning, our tour aims to immerse travelers in the natural splendor of the Cascades, offering interpretive insights into the area's ecological significance. The intent is to leave participants with a newfound appreciation for natural environments. Be advised, the tour includes hiking, tailored to ensure accessibility for all participants. 

This journey includes visits to two majestic waterfalls within the Cascade Mountains, offering an extraordinary venture into a temperate rainforest with the chance to witness colossal old-growth trees. We adhere to a precise schedule, returning by noon. Guests are advised to bring water and snacks during this morning-long, physically engaging experience.

review.name: Worth it!
review.reviewBody: It surpassed my expectations our tour guide Jonny was awesome! Although the hike did say "easy" it was a little rough on the knees being there were uphill parts to hike. But, Jonny was very patient with us slower hikers and encouraging. He even went above and beyond, Taking amazing pictures of us on our adventure. I would highly recommend this! It felt like hiking with friends definitely a great tour! And the amazing views so worth it!

review.name: Exceeded our expectations!
review.reviewBody: Our guide was very knowledgeable and informative. He customized the experience to our needs. The area was beautiful and our guide knew the best areas to stop for gorgeous photos.

itemListElement.name: 2 Day Mt Rainier All-Inclusive Small Group Tour

name: 2 Day Mt Rainier All-Inclusive Small Group Tour
description:
No two tours with us are the same! Our guides craft itineraries that reflect the best of what the Park has to offer that day, including group interests and dynamics. Please note that the itinerary outlined is a sample of potential destinations that could be included in the tour.
Experience Mount Rainier's highlights on a 2 day tailored to you. Our TripAdvisor "Hall of Fame" guides run the only tours permitted to explore more than a mile from the park road as the National Park is ecologically important & delicate. The U.S. Park Service restricts other tour companies - our competitors offer "road tours." We are professional nature educators (not just bus drivers) that have dedicated our lives to artful travel. Our all-inclusive small-group trip is limited to just 9 travelers.

review.name: A gift from my parents........
review.reviewBody:
Couldn't have been better!  My purpose was to spread my parents' ashes at Paradise, per my dad's request.  Kenzi was very helpful in navigating the "process" of spreading ashes (yes, it takes paperwork with the park) and figuring out a good time to do it! 
 Although this trip was more expensive than I would normally do, I felt that the comfort of knowing that EVERYTHING was taken care of would be worth it.  I'm fairly recently widowed and still figuring out how to travel solo without having an anxiety attack!

Our guide, Evan, was spectacular.  We were treated like royalty and I really appreciated his knowledge of the mountain and area. As promised, I didn't have to worry about a thing.  
 
I would 100% book with this company again and have already recommended it to my daughter and son-in-law.

review.name: Worth it!!
review.reviewBody: This was such a wonderful trip! What a unique opportunity to have a guide show us different trails and nature details about the mountain ands the park. Evan was fantastic! Totally worth the cost-- to have them plan every detail for us. And to get a rare reservation at the Paradise Inn.

itemListElement.name: Whale Watching + Deception Pass Tour from Seattle

name: Whale Watching + Deception Pass Tour from Seattle
description:
The ONLY Whale Watching tour with hotel pickup in Seattle!

Most whale sightings in the Puget Sound happen near the San Juan Islands - make the most of your day and explore Deception Pass before your Whale-watching cruise!

Journey north of Seattle to Deception Pass State Park, a Pacific Northwest hidden gem with views that rival our National Parks! Explore the old growth forest among the jagged cliffs and secret coastlines before enjoying a seasonal catered picnic lunch. After lunch, we'll drive up to Anacortes and join our partners, Outer Island Excursions, on a 3-hour Wildlife and Whale Watching boat tour. The Outer Island Excursions Captain and Naturalist will share information about the Salish Sea while we cruise around the channels in search of whales and other wildlife. Our all-inclusive small-group day trip is limited to 10 travelers. We also bring assorted snacks, water, and other cold beverages for the day. Don’t worry about a thing.

review.name: Gorgeous and enjoyable excursion
review.reviewBody:
I had an excellent experience on this tour!  It exceeded all expectations.  I am visiting Seattle for a conference (solo) and booked the trip to ensure I maximized my time here.  Our tour guide, Matthew, was very adept and working with our group of 9 to set the pace, tone and areas of focus for our excursions.  The vibe was fun but low key- perfect for me!

The scenery and wildlife are obviously spectacular.  What made this trip was the knowledge of our guide, the organization of the tour company and the special touches along the way.

I knew lunch was included but did not expect an elegant lunch of high quality food complete with silverware and table linens.  Yummy snacks and drinks were provided throughout the entire day (which just about reached 11 hours round trip).

The van was extremely comfortable, as was the whale watching ship.  I tend to have motion sickness.  I took a non-drowsy dramamine in the morning and never felt sick once.  Both the van and the ship were very stable.  

Extra bonus stars for our impromptu journey at the end of the tour to find Elsie Mae the Elephant Seal in Anacortes.  While you can't operate on a wild animal's schedule, the fact that Matthew seized the opportunity to view this special creature speaks volumes to the dedication Evergreen Escapes has to providing enjoyment and education, not just hauling people from Point A to Point B.  If I am lucky enough to visit Seattle again I will absolutely be booking with this company.

itemListElement.name: Mid-Day & Sunset Sailing on Seattle's Majestic Puget Sound

name: Mid-Day & Sunset Sailing on Seattle's Majestic Puget Sound
description:
Experience the magic of being carried by the wind, just as Peter Puget was when he mapped these waters back in 1792. From Seattle’s Shilshole Bay Marina we sail west across Puget Sound toward the magnificent Olympic Mountains. Along the way we will watch for orcas, schools of our local porpoises, sea lions, harbor seals, bald eagles, great blue herons, and other wildlife. On the Sunset Cruise, we’ll enjoy the light show as the sun drops behind the well-named Mount Olympus and other peaks in the Olympic Range and illuminates feathery horizon clouds into glorious colors.

Captain Grant, who holds a 100-ton Master of Inland Waters License from the U.S. Coast Guard, is dedicated to sharing the joy of being on the water with others. A former reporter for the Seattle Times, former Science and Medical writer for the Associated Press, and author of four books (one of which was named one of the year’s 10 Best nonfiction books by the American Library Association) Grant is a natural story teller.

review.name: What a treat!
review.reviewBody: Definitely a great time - highly recommend! Grant's attentiveness to the details makes this the best value. Wildlife surprises, opportunity to drive the boat, comfort offerings of jackets and refreshments, WOW. Highlight of our  trip.

review.name: Highly recommend!
review.reviewBody: My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed taking this sailboat cruise around the Puget. We saw a bunch of dolphins, seals, and jellyfish. There were even two cruise ships that left Seattle, which were great to see how big those ships are. Grant was a great captain and very friendly and laidback. He answered all of our questions and also enjoyed the peacefulness of being out on the water. Highly recommend, you will enjoy this trip!

review.name: Good times on the sound
review.reviewBody: This was an amazing experience. It was full of fun, and I felt safe on the sailboat. Grant was an excellent host and couldn't have asked for more. What an amazing time!

review.name: Fun and Relaxing
review.reviewBody:
My husband and I really enjoyed our sailing adventure with Grant. It was overcast and calm so it was easy to spot salmon and dolphins on the water. We saw dozens of seals by the rocks near the marina, too. 

Grant was a terrific guide and host for the afternoon. We loved being out on the water with him!

review.name: Experience a beautiful day on the water
review.reviewBody: Grant was phenomenal, extremely knowledgeable, personable and created an exceptional experience for each of us.  The scenery was spectacular and he complimented the trip with his wonderful demeanor and by taking pictures of us navigating the sailboat—what a treat.  If you want to enjoy Puget Sound and the beauty it has to offer—book a trip with Grant and make some wonderful memories!😊

review.name: Excellent experience for family and friends!
review.reviewBody: Excellent time for all!  As a captain myself I can honestly say Grant operates an extremely safe and immensely enjoyable charter!  With the latest USCG approved safety equipment and to note, not the cheap uncomfortable life preservers but he has the type that inflate during an emergency which are so comfortable you actually forget you are wearing them. I have booked a number of trips with Grant to take friends out and each time as soon as we boarded the wonderful experience started.  Grant is full of wonderful stories that he shares and as an accomplished writer is full of interesting facts of not only the Seattle maritime but things as varied as artificial intelligence and robotics.  Once out of the marina Grant encouraged everyone on board to take a turn at the helm while under his watchful eye and guiding each guest how to pilot the boat.  I highly recommend Grant for a wonderful daysail with friends!

review.name: Sailed Around
review.reviewBody: The views were incredible and Grant is such a sweet man. Everyone was able to help steer the boat and the sunset views were picture perfect.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Terrors Ghost Tour By US Ghost Adventures

name: Seattle Terrors Ghost Tour By US Ghost Adventures
description:
Embark on a thrilling journey through Seattle's shadowy streets with our immersive walking ghost tour, where history and haunting entwine.

Led by an expert local guide, this tour will lead you to some of the most iconic and eerie locations in the city.

As you navigate the atmospheric alleys and historic sites, you'll hear chilling tales of spirits that still haunt the shadows, from the restless souls of the Suquamish Burial Grounds to the dark legends of the Butterworth Building. Every stop is steeped in history, revealing the ghostly echoes of the past.

Prepare to be awed as you traverse a mile of spooky ground, where every corner unveils a new tale of the supernatural. Explore sites like Union Street, Post Alley, and the infamous Gum Wall, where the whispers of the past linger in the air.

Though entry into private buildings isn't allowed, you'll stand on truly haunted ground.

Join us for an evening of chills, and discover why Seattle is one of America's most haunted cities.

brand.name: Seattle Terrors By Us Ghost Adv...

review.name: Scary and historical
review.reviewBody: We had Zach as our guide. He was terrific. This was a uniquely chilling ghost tour and an excellent walk through Seattle history.

review.name: Just so-so
review.reviewBody: This tour was ok but felt a bit overpriced for only 1 hour...the information was ok but felt like someone reading a script and rushing from one sentence to the next in order to finish asap.

review.name: Spooky fun— even in March!
review.reviewBody: Oh it was so much fun! I’ve lived in Seattle for 7 years and had no idea that there was so much creepy history. Very educational and will be an option when different family and friends visit.

review.name: Great time!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Michael was engaging and knowledgeable. His stories brought the spooky and surreal history of Seattle to life. It was a fantastic evening!

review.name: Information filled spooky storytelling
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide was great at spooky storytelling, learned a lot! Definitely would recommend for others to try and super interested to know the extended tour entails.

review.name: Wasn’t scary but we enjoyed it
review.reviewBody: We enjoyed our tour and learning about the various “haunts”. Our guide was super nice and it was nice seeing that they part of the city so quiet

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: Great time, the guide was very knowledgeable! We enjoyed all of the information that was provided and the spookiness. Would definitely recommend to anyone visiting the city for the first time

review.name: More than generally satisfied.
review.reviewBody: Lively host to give a hidden historical gems behind Seattle's present! Buildings previously had been in different; 'rather somehow gruelsome', use was amusing and inspiring to gauge the city's potential😆

review.name: Very informational
review.reviewBody: Our guide was fantastic (Christine).  She was very knowledgeable and even gave us an extra bonus tour at the end despite the pouring rain. The tour is very informational but not overly exciting.

review.name: Fantastic experience!
review.reviewBody: Rob was a really good tour leader, one of the best tours I’ve taken. Good stories, nice range of historical and modern takes.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Walking Tours with a Local Guide: Private & Personalized

name: Seattle Walking Tours with a Local Guide: Private & Personalized
description:
Experience the diverse and eclectic city of Seattle with a local Seattle host who will create an itinerary based upon your schedule and interests. So don't let time constraints put you off. Whether you have one or two hours or a full day to spare, you’ll discover local gems and well-known anecdotes as you stroll through places like Pike Place Market or a local neighborhood like Fremont. See the city sites and enjoy a meal in the Chinatown-International district. You could even swing by Bad Jimmy’s, one of the lesser-known breweries loved by locals.

Our handpicked hosts are culinary connoisseurs and history buffs, bakers and bankers, students and seniors. Like the people who travel with us, they have different backgrounds and interests – but they’re all so passionate about the place they call home, they choose to spend their free time sharing it with the like-minded travelers matched to them.

Your meeting place and time as well as your itinerary are also flexible.

name: Knife Skills Workshop
description:
We’ll prepare one of two seasonal and creative meals all while honing in on our knife skills. Learn basic and advanced knife techniques and cuts such as dice, mince, on a bias, julienne, and more, as well as an overview of knife safety and care. No matter the time of year, we will demonstrate how to break down a whole chicken (or other poultry) and a whole fish from start to finish! We’ll then cook off our proteins as a group.

Class price includes skilled instructors, all supplies needed, and a full meal! Accommodations for dietary restrictions made upon request.

name: Ramen from Scratch
description: Nothing beats fresh ramen - from springy noodles to umami rich broth to a myriad classic and unique toppings! Join us in this hands-on cooking class all about ramen!

itemListElement.name: 2-Hours Knife Skills Cooking Class in Seattle with Instructor

name: 2-Hours Knife Skills Cooking Class in Seattle with Instructor
description: Dive into the fundamentals of knife skills in cooking! We’ll prepare a seasonal Mediterranean meal all while honing in on our knife skills.
